cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on developing a tool to analyze the relation between natural language words and APIs, which involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also addresses challenges related to software engineering (SE), such as acquiring massive words and APIs for mining and improving comparison algorithms. Thus, cs.SE is also a likely sub-category. The paper proposes a novel approach to modeling words and APIs simultaneously using word embedding techniques, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories.
